citation.case_name: Wabash R. Co. v. Commercial Transport, Inc.

html:
361 U.S. 1

80 S.Ct. 50

4 L.Ed.2d 49

WABASH R. R. CO., et al.
v.
COMMERCIAL TRANSPORT, INC., et al.

No. 68.

Supreme Court of the United States

October 12, 1959

Messrs. Eugene S. Davis, Urchie B. Ellis, J. L. Lenihan and Amos M. Mathews, for appellants.

Mr. Mack Stephenson, for appellee Commercial Transport, Inc.

Solicitor General Rankin, Acting Assistant Attorney General Bicks, Messrs. Charles H. Weston and Henry Geller, for the United States.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motions to affirm are granted and the judgment is affirmed.
